<br>
I've been on 4 hate raids in the last couple of weeks, and there has been a rather sad sight at our second campsite: a poor dead elven cleric halfway clad in purple. For the first three raids, she wasn't online. For the fourth raid, she logged back in much after we had cleared that area. Turns out about half the raid force had added her to their /friends list just to check and see when she might be online again...as soon as she logged in, our puller cleared out the patrol again and dragged her corpse up to 2nd floor for a rez.<br>
<br>
It was too late for any experience gain, but at least all that gear was preserved.<br>
<br>
-----<br>
<br>
Other &quot;I'm all alone out here&quot; amusing Hate stories:<br>
<br>
*) On one Hate raid, a paladin in my group went AFK immediately after buffing at the break-in camp. He was still AFK when we had to move camp, so I threw Invis on him and COTH-ed him to the new campsite when we got settled in. Ditto for our next move to the Organ Hall. Finally he came back online...turns out that someone in his apartment complex had a cooking accident and set fire to half the building. He had to evacuate his building and answer a few questions with the authorities before he could go back in and rejoin the raid.<br>
<br>
*) On my very first hate raid, we had just called the raid on Second Floor and killed the last mob. My cable company decided that would be an excellent time to do router maintenance. No one on the raid even realized I was gone, they assumed I gated out since the raid was over. The next morning I logged in to a desolate plane, sat down, memmed gate, and got out of their quickly. It's a wonder I was in enough of an isolated place that I didn't get aggro.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usawzallz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sawzallz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#333333>(6/21/02 2:23:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=251.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: CR in hate</span><hr size=1> I somehow amassed a small rescue party the following morning.....people never cease to amaze me just when you think everyone is out for their own good something like this happens and you realize just how many great people there really is out there... nice to have my faith in humanity restored a big THANK YOU to all that helped me<br>
<br>
Was about to stop answering random calls to help people with epic mobs and such but not now.  <p>
